    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen running `:checkhealth` while using `vim._extui`, \"Running healthchecks...\" will appear after the checks have finished running instead of while they are running.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- `nvim --clean`\n- `:lua require('vim._extui').enable { enable = true, msg = { target = 'cmd', timeout = 4000 } }`\n- `:checkhealth`\n\n\"Running healthchecks...\" will not appear while the health checks are running, but after they are finished running, the text will appear in the command-line.\n\n<img width=\"865\" height=\"561\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/1bf2ac47-4e60-443c-b3bb-83d4828dfbbd\" />\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWithout enabling `vim._extui`:\n\n<img width=\"865\" height=\"561\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/53609072-cc3d-44b9-aba3-c85673fe375e\" />\n\n\"Running healthchecks...\" will appear while the health checks are running, and disappears afterwards.\n\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev+1466-a04c73ca0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnon-applicable\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora 42\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.42.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nhttps://copr.fedorainfracloud.org/coprs/agriffis/neovim-nightly/",
